programme.title: The Catch-Up Show: Season So Far
programme.desc: As the Premier League takes a break, the Catch-Up Show brings you the best features to air across Premier League programming this season.

programme.title: PL Stories: Eduardo da Silva
programme.desc: Eduardo da Silva will forever be synonymous for suffering one of the worst injuries in Premier League history. We travelled to Brazil, Croatia and caught up with the former Arsenal hero here in England to find out more about the man who gave Gunners fans a fleeting glimpse of greatness before being so cruelly deprived.

programme.title: The Big Interview: Luis Garcia
programme.desc: Arriving on Merseyside in 2004 as part of a freshly recruited Spanish contingent to help build a new-look Liverpool side, Luis Garcia soon became a cult hero at Anfield. But it wasn’t always plain sailing for the Catalonian. In this week’s Big Interview, Garcia shares the difficulties he faced adjusting to the Premier League, how Rafa Benitez managed to hone his talents and his thoughts on that famous “ghost” goal against Chelsea in the 2005 Champions League semi-final.(n)
